snippet.textDisplay:
This has NOTHING to do with the character of Djokovic. This whole fiasco has been caused by the initial awarding of a visa by the federal government of Australia, by the home affairs department, to be precise. The federal government (border control) then decided to tear up the visa. Judge Kelly agreed that Djokovic had complied with ALL entry requirements including the medical exemption. The medical exemption criteria include having had a positive Covid test within the previous 6 months. These criteria were/are defined by ATAGI, and the immigration laws specifically state that medical exemptions are as defined by ATAGI. That prompted judge Kelly to state (I watched the entire case) that there are unanswered questions about why the visa was rejected. He also stated ‘what else could Djokovic have done?’  Furthermore he stated that ATAGI rules trumps border control in this case.
So….judge Kelly did not rule ONLY on a procedural matter as the press would like all to believe. 
If the politicians want ti change ATAGI rules, then they should do so asap before someone else waists their time/money and lands in a detention center.
Another point: If a super healthy individual who has tested positive twice (mid 2020 and again in Dec 2021) is a health danger to the Australian people (seriously???) then why is the Australian Open not cancelled??!!
Ok, last point: Being double vaccinated, double boosted DOES NOT prevent the transmission of sars-cov-2.
